== Test 3

The charts below give information about a public library in a town called Little Chalfont.

#figure(image("/img/cam20T3-1.png", width: 80%))

Summarise the information by selecting and reporting the main features, and make comparisons where relevant.]


#作文(words: 215, timing: 40, date: "2025-12-09")[The charts give 3 kind of information about Little Chalfont Library. #issue[][缺少一个清晰的总体概述]

1. #issue[][正式雅思写作通过自然段落组织内容，不要使用编号。] Membership #praise[breakdown][准确的学术词汇] by age group. As of 2016, more than half (51%) of the library's members are adults from 18 to 64 years of age. The next largest group is children under 13 which takes up 22% of total membership, followed by teenagers under 18 (15%), then older adults over 64 (12%).

2. Book loans breakdown by category. In accordance with the age group breakdown of the same year, the most popular loans are adult fiction and children's fiction, each taking 38% of total loans. For adults, the next favorable categories are adult non-fiction (13%) and adult audio books (2%). As for children, they also prefer non-fiction (6%), followed by children's DVDs (1%). The young adults category only #typo[account][三单accounts] for 2% of the total loans, much less than their membership proportion, #praise[in contrast][有意义的比较] to children whose loans exceed by far their membership.

3. Total number of loans from 2007 to 2016. We can see from the bar chart that the library's total loans grew from #issue[a bit][避免口语用词] over 15,000 in 2007 to just above 20,000 in 2011 before it declined somewhat to under 20,000 in 2013. Then the loans increased again steadily up until 2016 at around 22,000, #issue[where the data is truncated][不必要的主观推测].]

